As he was walking, he saw Levi, the son of Alphaeus. Levi was sitting at the tax collector's place. Jesus said to him, "Follow me." Levi got up and followed him.
Later, Jesus was having dinner at Levi's house. Many tax collectors and "sinners" were eating with him and with his disciples. They were part of the large crowd that followed Jesus.
There were some teachers of the law who were Pharisees present. They saw Jesus eating with "sinners" and tax collectors. They asked his disciples, "Why does he eat with tax collectors and 'sinners'?"
Jesus heard this. He said to them, "Those who are well do not need a doctor, but the sick do. I did not come to call the righteous who think they are right with God to follow me. I came to call sinners to follow me." They asked Jesus about fasting.
The disciples of John and the Pharisees were fasting and not eating. Some people came to Jesus. They said to him, "John's disciples are fasting. The Pharisees' disciples are also fasting. But your disciples are not fasting. Why are they not fasting?"
Jesus answered, "How can the guests of the bridegroom go without eating while he is with them? They will not fast as long as he is with them.
