Healing on Saturday
Once again, Jesus went to the synagogue. There was a man who had a weak and crooked hand.
There were some Pharisees looking for a fault in Jesus. They were watching him closely. They wanted to see if he would heal the man on the Sabbath.
Jesus spoke to the man whose hand was weak and crooked. He said to him: "Stand before all the people."
Then Isa asked them, "What does the law say we must do on the Sabbath? Should we do good? Or evil? Should we save life? Or kill?" But no one answered.
Jesus looked at them with anger. He was very upset because their hearts were stubborn. Then he said to the man, "Stretch out your hand." He stretched it out, and his hand became like new.
Afterwards, the Pharisees went out and began making plans with the Herodians. They wanted to kill Jesus. The crowds were following Jesus.
Jesus walked to the Sea of Galilee with his disciples. A large crowd from Galilee followed him.
